00:09:34,325 --> 00:09:35,409
would be ludicrous.

265
00:09:35,618 --> 00:09:36,786
Boris Sokolov's death,

266
00:09:36,994 --> 00:09:39,872
while undoubtedly tragic,

267
00:09:40,081 --> 00:09:41,290
changes nothing.

268
00:09:42,333 --> 00:09:44,293
Well, the defense agrees.

269
00:09:44,752 --> 00:09:45,503
What?

270
00:09:46,003 --> 00:09:48,297
His death doesn't
change a single thing.

271
00:09:48,506 --> 00:09:50,883
With or without
Mr. Sokolov's testimony,

272
00:09:51,092 --> 00:09:52,552
my client should never
have been charged

273
00:09:52,760 --> 00:09:53,719
with these crimes.

274
00:09:55,304 --> 00:09:55,930
Well...

275
00:09:56,138 --> 00:09:58,349
seeing as both parties agree,

276
00:09:58,558 --> 00:09:59,976
the trial will proceed
immediately.

277
00:10:00,184 --> 00:10:00,977
Actually, Your Honor,

278
00:10:01,185 --> 00:10:02,311
the State would like to, uh,

279
00:10:02,520 --> 00:10:03,729
request a continuance.

280
00:10:04,647 --> 00:10:06,107
In light of the death
of our key witness,

281
00:10:06,315 --> 00:10:08,526
our office needs time
to, uh, reexamine

282
00:10:09,026 --> 00:10:09,819
its strategy.

283
00:10:10,027 --> 00:10:11,153
But I'm confused,
Your Honor.

284
00:10:11,362 --> 00:10:12,863
Didn't we just hear
the prosecution say

285
00:10:13,072 --> 00:10:14,740
their case was
"unshakable"?

286
00:10:15,324 --> 00:10:16,784
We did.

287
00:10:16,993 --> 00:10:18,202
Request denied.

288
00:10:18,911 --> 00:10:20,955
Session will resume after lunch.

289
00:10:26,586 --> 00:10:28,087
What the hell are you doing,
Mother?

290
00:10:28,296 --> 00:10:29,422
Oh, calm down, Lucifer.

291
00:10:29,630 --> 00:10:31,048
This isn't pleasant
for me, either.

292
00:10:31,257 --> 00:10:33,092
Oh, yes, I can see
you're suffering terribly.

293
00:10:33,301 --> 00:10:35,344
I was good up there,
wasn't I?

294
00:10:35,553 --> 00:10:37,763
Not sure why humans spend
so much time in law school.

295
00:10:37,972 --> 00:10:38,806
Two nights seemed plenty.

296
00:10:39,015 --> 00:10:39,765
Mum.

297
00:10:40,474 --> 00:10:43,019
I had to find a way
to open your eyes.

298
00:10:43,227 --> 00:10:45,062
You need to see that
this Chloe you so adore

299
00:10:45,271 --> 00:10:46,105
isn't worthy of you.

300
00:10:46,314 --> 00:10:47,064
(scoffs)

301
00:10:47,273 --> 00:10:48,733
I admit I enjoy working
with her, but adore,

302
00:10:48,941 --> 00:10:49,609
that's a bit much.

303
00:10:49,817 --> 00:10:52,028
Oh, please. You've sacrificed
more for her

304
00:10:52,236 --> 00:10:53,779
than you ever have
for anyone else.

305
00:10:54,655 --> 00:10:56,657
Have you forgotten?
You killed your brother,

306
00:10:56,866 --> 00:10:58,284
my son, to protect her.

307
00:10:58,784 --> 00:11:01,537
Do you think there's anything
even remotely similar

308
00:11:01,746 --> 00:11:02,538
that she would do for you?

309
00:11:03,623 --> 00:11:04,540
I suppose...

310
00:11:05,458 --> 00:11:06,167
I don't know.

311
00:11:06,375 --> 00:11:08,336
Well, if all goes according
to plan in that courtroom,

312
00:11:08,544 --> 00:11:09,420
you will know.

313
00:11:09,629 --> 00:11:11,005
Know that she doesn't
deserve you,

314
00:11:11,213 --> 00:11:12,423
because she doesn't
care about you

315
00:11:12,632 --> 00:11:13,966
like you care about her.

316
00:11:14,175 --> 00:11:16,594
You need to see that you're
not meant to be together.

317
00:11:17,219 --> 00:11:18,220
You belong with your family.

318
00:11:18,429 --> 00:11:19,889
Which is why
I have to do this.

319
00:11:20,097 --> 00:11:21,682
Do what, Mum?

320
00:11:24,518 --> 00:11:26,354
What sort of evil plan
are you concocting?

321
00:11:26,562 --> 00:11:28,731
And please don't tell me
it began by killing Boris.

322
00:11:29,190 --> 00:11:30,775
Oh, actually, that was
just a happy twist of fate.

323
00:11:30,983 --> 00:11:32,068
I was gonna
blow Chloe up,

324
00:11:32,276 --> 00:11:33,361
but Amenadiel
talked me out of it.

325
00:11:33,569 --> 00:11:34,862
You what?!

326
00:11:35,613 --> 00:11:37,990
Mother, I swear,
if you hurt her, I will rip--

327
00:11:38,199 --> 00:11:40,660
Well, looks like
your brother was right.

328
00:11:42,662 --> 00:11:45,247
Just promise me that
you won't touch her.

329
00:11:47,583 --> 00:11:49,752
I'm not going to hurt anyone.

330
00:11:55,549 --> 00:11:57,468
Lucifer, you promise me,

331
00:11:57,927 --> 00:12:00,096
whatever that was, that
it doesn't affect the trial.

332
00:12:00,304 --> 00:12:02,431
First of all, Detective,
there is no "that."

333
00:12:02,765 --> 00:12:05,518
And secondly, rest assured,
everything will be okay.

334
00:12:06,977 --> 00:12:08,145
I've got this.

335
00:12:16,821 --> 00:12:18,531
You looking for Boris'
forensics report?

336
00:12:18,739 --> 00:12:19,532
(sighs)

337
00:12:20,199 --> 00:12:20,908
Uh-huh.

338
00:12:21,492 --> 00:12:22,326
Hasn't come in yet.

339
00:12:22,535 --> 00:12:23,828
Ella should have it
any minute now.

340
00:12:24,745 --> 00:12:26,789
I know this isn't my case,
but I'm freaking out, Dan.

341
00:12:26,997 --> 00:12:28,416
I can't let Perry get
away with everything.

342
00:12:28,624 --> 00:12:29,458
You won't.

343
00:12:29,834 --> 00:12:31,627
You didn't see Charlotte
Richards in court today.

344
00:12:31,836 --> 00:12:32,628
(high-pitched): Char--?
(clears his throat)

345
00:12:32,837 --> 00:12:34,004
I'm sorry. Uh,

346
00:12:34,213 --> 00:12:36,048
Charlotte Richards
is, uh, defending Perry?

347
00:12:36,507 --> 00:12:37,133
Yeah.

348
00:12:37,341 --> 00:12:39,135
Really?
She's that good?

349
00:12:39,343 --> 00:12:41,053
Yes, she's
the best.

350
00:12:41,262 --> 00:12:43,055
Which is why it would
be helpful if we could--

351
00:12:43,264 --> 00:12:45,057
Well, if you could tie
Perry to Boris' murder.

352
00:12:45,266 --> 00:12:47,601
Okay, well, motive
and M.O. line up.

353
00:12:48,060 --> 00:12:49,437
Boris' tongue was cut out.

354
00:12:49,770 --> 00:12:52,440
So the killer was sending
a really clear message--

355
00:12:52,648 --> 00:12:54,567
loose lips get
their head clipped.

356
00:12:55,317 --> 00:12:57,361
Perry did this so Boris
couldn't testify, I know it.

357
00:12:57,653 --> 00:12:59,572
But hasn't he been behind bars
since you arrested him?

358
00:12:59,780 --> 00:13:00,906
Yeah, but he could have
orchestrated it in prison.

359
00:13:01,115 --> 00:13:02,074
It's also his M.O.

360
00:13:02,283 --> 00:13:03,993
Exactly, and if Perry
is good at anything,

361
00:13:04,201 --> 00:13:05,661
it's making other people
pay for his crimes.

362
00:13:05,870 --> 00:13:07,580
Okay, well, whoever
Perry hired to do this

363
00:13:07,788 --> 00:13:08,789
was one sharp dude.

364
00:13:08,998 --> 00:13:11,500
The cut on Boris' neck
is extremely precise.

365
00:13:11,876 --> 00:13:14,503
I'm thinking industrial-size
professional slicer.

366
00:13:15,087 --> 00:13:18,340
Listen, I'm gonna do
everything I can to find him.

367
00:13:18,758 --> 00:13:20,342
Even if I have to interview
the owner

368
00:13:20,551 --> 00:13:22,052
of every single
meat slicer in L.A.

369
00:13:22,261 --> 00:13:23,637
ELLA:
You won't have to.

370
00:13:23,846 --> 00:13:27,141
There was also
non-human DNA on Boris.

371
00:13:27,349 --> 00:13:28,517
Swine, to be exact.

372
00:13:28,726 --> 00:13:31,020
A unique cross-bred
for its delicious meat.

373
00:13:31,228 --> 00:13:33,481
And there's only
one place that sells it.

374
00:13:37,234 --> 00:13:38,110
Ah!

375
00:13:38,694 --> 00:13:39,403
Hi.

376
00:13:39,945 --> 00:13:41,697
That's so sweet of you, but you
don't have to stick around.

377
00:13:41,906 --> 00:13:43,157
- Trials can be so boring.
- Well,

378
00:13:43,365 --> 00:13:44,116
not this one.

379
00:13:44,700 --> 00:13:45,326
What do you mean?

380
00:13:45,534 --> 00:13:46,494
Mr. Morningstar,

381
00:13:47,411 --> 00:13:48,078
we're ready for you.

382
00:13:48,287 --> 00:13:50,247
Wonderful.
Lovely. Right.

383
00:13:50,748 --> 00:13:53,459
Off I go to shield you from
that Quid Pro Ho, Detective.

384
00:13:54,794 --> 00:13:55,920
Lucifer, what are you doing?

385
00:13:56,128 --> 00:13:58,047
Well, I figured
there's no reason for us

386
00:13:58,255 --> 00:14:00,800
to lose our heads just
because Boris lost his.

387
00:14:02,885 --> 00:14:05,971
I swear to tell the truth,
the whole truth,

388
00:14:06,388 --> 00:14:08,182
and nothing but the truth,

389
00:14:08,933 --> 00:14:10,601
so help me Dad.

390
00:14:19,026 --> 00:14:20,152
Mr. Morningstar,

391
00:14:20,361 --> 00:14:22,947
you were there
when Boris was arrested.

392
00:14:23,155 --> 00:14:25,032
Right? Working with
Detective Espinoza.

393
00:14:26,408 --> 00:14:27,117
That is correct.

394
00:14:27,326 --> 00:14:28,786
Except I call him
Detective Douche.

395
00:14:28,994 --> 00:14:30,120
(laughter)

396
00:14:30,329 --> 00:14:31,580
But that's another story.

397
00:14:32,832 --> 00:14:34,708
So would you
please describe to us

398
00:14:34,917 --> 00:14:35,876
what happened?

399
00:14:36,085 --> 00:14:37,169
Yes, I'd love to, actually.

400
00:14:37,378 --> 00:14:38,337
May-may I have the floor?

401
00:14:38,546 --> 00:14:39,213
By all means.

402
00:14:39,421 --> 00:14:40,548
LUCIFER:
Thank you.

403
00:14:41,257 --> 00:14:43,050
I'm going to need...

404
00:14:43,801 --> 00:14:44,802
Hello.

405
00:14:45,219 --> 00:14:46,303
May I borrow your scarf?

406
00:14:46,512 --> 00:14:48,639
Your Honor,
is this necessary?

407
00:14:48,848 --> 00:14:50,850
Well, you want
the full story, don't you?

408
00:14:51,016 --> 00:14:52,893
I mean, the Devil's
in the details.

409
00:14:54,103 --> 00:14:55,145
Thank you ever so much.

410
00:14:56,480 --> 00:14:59,066
Right. Myself
and Detective Douche--

411
00:14:59,275 --> 00:15:00,776
sorry, Detective Espinoza--

412
00:15:00,985 --> 00:15:02,444
were asked by the LAPD

413
00:15:02,653 --> 00:15:03,863
to perform a sting operation.

414
00:15:04,488 --> 00:15:05,197
Not the singer.

415
00:15:05,406 --> 00:15:07,867
- (laughter)
- So we had to go undercover

416
00:15:08,075 --> 00:15:09,034
at Boris' bathhouse.

417
00:15:09,243 --> 00:15:10,578
Guns of steel...

418
00:15:10,786 --> 00:15:12,413
Got up there...
(imitated slashing sound)

419
00:15:12,621 --> 00:15:13,914
Walked over like
he's constantly got

420
00:15:14,123 --> 00:15:15,499
a gun between his legs...

421
00:15:15,708 --> 00:15:18,419
Boris looked me in the eye,
and he said,

422
00:15:18,627 --> 00:15:20,504
(Russian accent): "People call
me human lie detector."

423
00:15:20,713 --> 00:15:21,547
He was going to kill...

424
00:15:21,755 --> 00:15:24,216
Shook my hand like
some kind of Roman warrior...

425
00:15:24,425 --> 00:15:27,469
...and it was sealed, and I
handed over the investigation

426
00:15:28,095 --> 00:15:29,680
to Detective Decker.

427
00:15:29,889 --> 00:15:31,181
- Thank you.
- (laughter, applause)

428
00:15:31,390 --> 00:15:32,516
♪ Stop draggin' me down ♪

429
00:15:32,725 --> 00:15:33,726
♪♪

430
00:15:34,518 --> 00:15:37,146
♪ Stop dragging me down, yeah. ♪

431
00:15:39,940 --> 00:15:40,774
DAN:
I got a question.

432
00:15:40,983 --> 00:15:42,735
Do you ever get the feeling
like you've been used?

433
00:15:42,943 --> 00:15:45,571
You mean, by--
oh, I don't know--

434
00:15:45,779 --> 00:15:49,575
the woman who's defending the
killer of your ex-wife's dad?

435
00:15:49,783 --> 00:15:50,618
What?

436
00:15:50,826 --> 00:15:52,494
Charlotte Richards is
the gorgeous lady

437
00:15:52,703 --> 00:15:53,662
you slept with, right?

438
00:15:54,038 --> 00:15:55,456
How the hell did
you know that?

439
00:15:55,998 --> 00:15:58,042
Well, I saw a long,
honey-blonde hair

440
00:15:58,250 --> 00:15:59,376
on your coat the other day.

441
00:15:59,585 --> 00:16:01,629
It was curlier than Chloe's.
And then,

442
00:16:01,837 --> 00:16:03,464
I spotted a smudge of lipstick

443
00:16:03,672 --> 00:16:05,382
on your cuff--
burgundy shade.

444
00:16:05,758 --> 00:16:08,552
Bold, but not too sexy.
Lawyer color.

445
00:16:09,428 --> 00:16:10,054
Really?

446
00:16:10,262 --> 00:16:12,765
No. I just saw
your butt pucker

447
00:16:12,973 --> 00:16:15,142
when Chloe mentioned her name
in the lab this morning.

448
00:16:15,351 --> 00:16:16,226
God.

449
00:16:17,311 --> 00:16:18,771
Why are you so worried?

450
00:16:18,979 --> 00:16:20,564
I mean, you didn't tell her
anything about the case

451
00:16:20,773 --> 00:16:22,441
that she could
use in court, right?

452
00:16:22,650 --> 00:16:24,693
- I don't think so, but...
- There you go.

453
00:16:25,694 --> 00:16:26,987
- Mezcal cocktails, man.

454
00:16:27,196 --> 00:16:28,948
Oof. Those sneak up on you.

455
00:16:29,156 --> 00:16:30,991
She did keep wanting
to talk about our exes,

456
00:16:31,200 --> 00:16:33,202
and all I thought was, you know
what, she's so easy to talk to.

457
00:16:33,410 --> 00:16:34,328
She's so sympathetic.

458
00:16:34,536 --> 00:16:35,746
God, I'm such an idiot.

459
00:16:35,955 --> 00:16:37,831
- Hey...
- No, her taking Perry's case

460
00:16:38,040 --> 00:16:39,333
right after we...

461
00:16:39,833 --> 00:16:40,834
It can't be a coincidence.

462
00:16:41,293 --> 00:16:42,002
Why not?

463
00:16:43,212 --> 00:16:45,297
- Maybe she really
just likes you.
- Yeah.

464
00:16:45,506 --> 00:16:46,924
- WOMAN: 44.
- ELLA: Hi. We'll take

465
00:16:47,132 --> 00:16:49,468
the headless body of a dude
named Boris, please.

466
00:16:52,680 --> 00:16:53,973
I was going
to call you guys.

467
00:16:54,181 --> 00:16:56,058
I was just... scared.

468
00:16:56,809 --> 00:16:58,394
A few days ago,
this guy approached me.

469
00:16:59,019 --> 00:17:00,104
Big creepy dude.

470
00:17:00,312 --> 00:17:02,106
He demanded the keys to use
the equipment after hours.

471
00:17:02,314 --> 00:17:04,358
No questions asked,
unless I wanted

472
00:17:04,566 --> 00:17:05,693
to end up in the sausage myself.

473
00:17:05,901 --> 00:17:07,695
- Do you know his name?
- No.

474
00:17:08,821 --> 00:17:09,947
Asian, big.

475
00:17:10,364 --> 00:17:11,240
Very scary.

476
00:17:13,033 --> 00:17:17,037
But the scar on his neck
it's very distinctive.

477
00:17:17,997 --> 00:17:19,373
Thank you, Mr. Morningstar.

478
00:17:19,581 --> 00:17:21,542
What a, uh, vivid picture.

479
00:17:22,167 --> 00:17:24,378
It's almost as if Boris
himself just testified.

480
00:17:24,586 --> 00:17:26,672
JUDGE: (quietly): Except
a more handsome version.

481
00:17:26,880 --> 00:17:28,674
Oh, stop it, Judy.

482
00:17:28,882 --> 00:17:29,717
(chuckles)

483
00:17:29,925 --> 00:17:30,884
(clears throat)
Thank you.

484
00:17:32,052 --> 00:17:32,761
Right actually,
to that,

485
00:17:32,970 --> 00:17:34,263
I would like to add one
more thing, if I may...

486
00:17:34,471 --> 00:17:36,557
I think we've had
enough, Your Honor.

487
00:17:36,765 --> 00:17:38,392
Shh!
Please...

488
00:17:38,934 --> 00:17:40,519
continue Luc--

489
00:17:41,979 --> 00:17:42,980
Mr. Morningstar.

490
00:17:43,188 --> 00:17:44,481
Thank you, my darling.

491
00:17:45,899 --> 00:17:48,736
Yes, I'd just like to say,
for the record,

492
00:17:48,944 --> 00:17:52,781
the LAPD, and Detective Decker,
in particular,

493
00:17:53,115 --> 00:17:55,200
acted impeccably
on this case.

494
00:17:55,409 --> 00:17:58,454
This whole courtroom,
nay, the entire city

495
00:17:58,662 --> 00:18:01,081
can rest assured that
someone as honest,

496
00:18:01,290 --> 00:18:04,585
trustworthy, and reliable
as Detective Decker

497
00:18:04,793 --> 00:18:06,837
is out there
protecting them.

498
00:18:07,046 --> 00:18:10,257
She is... truly good.

499
00:18:12,092 --> 00:18:12,760
And I don't mean in bed.

500
00:18:12,968 --> 00:18:14,011
I wouldn't know.

501
00:18:14,887 --> 00:18:15,929
That's how good she is.

502
00:18:17,473 --> 00:18:18,265
Thank you.

503
00:18:19,516 --> 00:18:20,267
Miss Richards?

504
00:18:20,893 --> 00:18:21,894
Your witness.

505
00:18:25,689 --> 00:18:27,608
I have no questions
at this time.

506
00:18:29,693 --> 00:18:31,487
(thunder crashes)

507
00:18:41,121 --> 00:18:41,789
Hey!

508
00:18:41,997 --> 00:18:42,790
That's Chloe's car.

509
00:18:42,998 --> 00:18:43,874
What are you looking for?

510
00:18:44,083 --> 00:18:44,917
Hey.

511
00:18:46,210 --> 00:18:47,169
I was, um...

512
00:18:48,253 --> 00:18:48,879
You.

513
00:18:49,546 --> 00:18:50,631
I was looking for you.

514
00:18:51,757 --> 00:18:52,382
Really?

515
00:18:52,591 --> 00:18:53,759
Yeah, I've missed you.

516
00:18:56,178 --> 00:18:58,055
It's true, I still
think about you, Maze.

517
00:18:59,014 --> 00:19:01,433
Every day. And every time
that I see you, it's...

518
00:19:04,394 --> 00:19:05,562
I miss you, too.

519
00:19:14,196 --> 00:19:15,405
It's like fireworks, isn't it?

520
00:19:16,156 --> 00:19:17,324
(chuckles)

521
00:19:18,158 --> 00:19:19,326
But are you sure
that's the kind

522
00:19:19,535 --> 00:19:20,661
you're looking for?

523
00:19:25,624 --> 00:19:26,792
Or was it this?

524
00:19:31,171 --> 00:19:35,175
One-- tell your mother no one
is hurting Chloe on my watch.

