00:29:44,868 --> 00:29:45,994
She's terrifying.

782
00:29:46,494 --> 00:29:47,203
But what happens if we lose?

783
00:29:47,412 --> 00:29:48,413
They kill us.

784
00:29:48,621 --> 00:29:49,414
Well, you.

785
00:29:49,622 --> 00:29:50,790
'Cause I'm immortal.

786
00:29:50,999 --> 00:29:51,958
Right. Shall we?

787
00:29:52,167 --> 00:29:53,418
(punches)

788
00:29:53,626 --> 00:29:55,462
♪♪

789
00:29:56,921 --> 00:29:57,881
Choose your weapon.

790
00:29:58,298 --> 00:29:59,466
I choose those.

791
00:30:07,682 --> 00:30:08,516
You done?

792
00:30:09,476 --> 00:30:11,144
(punches, screams)

793
00:30:11,352 --> 00:30:12,228
(grunts)

794
00:30:14,355 --> 00:30:15,690
♪ I'm deep, I'm deep ♪

795
00:30:15,899 --> 00:30:18,693
♪ Deeper in the situation
that I ever thought I would be ♪

796
00:30:19,694 --> 00:30:21,237
♪ I be ♪

797
00:30:22,322 --> 00:30:23,573
♪ I see, I see ♪

798
00:30:23,782 --> 00:30:26,910
♪ My reflection is going,
this river is flowing on me ♪

799
00:30:30,747 --> 00:30:32,248
♪ It's raining ♪

800
00:30:32,707 --> 00:30:34,417
♪ She's playing ♪

801
00:30:34,626 --> 00:30:36,669
♪ I feel it from below
and I know ♪

802
00:30:36,878 --> 00:30:39,005
- ♪ The Devil's got a hold on me ♪
- Ooh!

803
00:30:39,214 --> 00:30:40,089
Hoo-ah.

804
00:30:47,013 --> 00:30:48,348
She likes that move.

805
00:30:48,556 --> 00:30:50,183
♪ The toll it's taking ♪

806
00:30:51,017 --> 00:30:52,519
♪ It's raining ♪

807
00:30:52,894 --> 00:30:54,312
♪ She's playing ♪

808
00:30:55,021 --> 00:30:56,981
♪ I've done it once
and I'll do it again ♪

809
00:30:57,190 --> 00:30:59,234
♪ The Devil's got a hold on me ♪

810
00:31:01,027 --> 00:31:01,653
(Kang exclaims)

811
00:31:01,861 --> 00:31:03,196
♪ Oh, on me ♪

812
00:31:05,281 --> 00:31:06,199
(crunches)

813
00:31:09,285 --> 00:31:10,370
(wolf whistles)

814
00:31:10,578 --> 00:31:11,371
Down, girl.

815
00:31:11,579 --> 00:31:12,539
Are you serious?

816
00:31:12,747 --> 00:31:14,833
Well, I mean, you did
get two new toys.

817
00:31:19,879 --> 00:31:20,547
Well, that sucked.

818
00:31:20,755 --> 00:31:21,714
Hmm?

819
00:31:23,466 --> 00:31:24,300
But a deal's a deal.

820
00:31:24,509 --> 00:31:26,135
LUCIFER: Indeed.
LI: The one you seek

821
00:31:26,344 --> 00:31:28,721
was banished for working
outside the family.

822
00:31:28,930 --> 00:31:30,765
We don't break bread
with strangers.

823
00:31:33,560 --> 00:31:34,727
You'll find him at this address.

824
00:31:37,272 --> 00:31:37,897
<i>Xie Xie.</i>

825
00:31:38,106 --> 00:31:39,732
- No problem.
- (exhales)

826
00:31:40,233 --> 00:31:43,236
See? Easy peasy, Chinese-y.

827
00:31:45,238 --> 00:31:45,864
CHLOE:
<i>Dan's got a lead</i>

828
00:31:46,072 --> 00:31:48,408
on Boris' killer,
and it may implicate Perry.

829
00:31:48,908 --> 00:31:50,869
So, if he is responsible,
it might not matter

830
00:31:51,077 --> 00:31:52,579
- what happens in this trial.
- (exhales)

831
00:31:52,787 --> 00:31:54,789
Well, that's great, 'cause we
are getting our asses kicked.

832
00:31:54,998 --> 00:31:56,291
Well. I have to testify next.

833
00:31:56,499 --> 00:31:57,667
I just hope I don't
make things worse.

834
00:31:57,917 --> 00:31:59,460
Oh, you'll do great, honey.
You're a pro.

835
00:32:00,128 --> 00:32:01,588
Right, Mom.
A real pro.

836
00:32:01,796 --> 00:32:03,089
Like when I followed
the prison van.

837
00:32:03,882 --> 00:32:05,884
Mom, what if I'm the reason
Dad's killer goes free?

838
00:32:06,092 --> 00:32:07,218
Don't you dare.

839
00:32:07,427 --> 00:32:09,429
No father in the world was
more proud of his daughter

840
00:32:09,637 --> 00:32:10,555
than your dad.

841
00:32:11,306 --> 00:32:13,016
And nothing you could do
in that courtroom

842
00:32:13,224 --> 00:32:15,101
or anywhere
will ever change that.

843
00:32:15,310 --> 00:32:16,603
(footsteps)

844
00:32:16,811 --> 00:32:18,062
I just miss him.

845
00:32:18,813 --> 00:32:21,190
I want him to get
the justice he deserves.

846
00:32:22,233 --> 00:32:24,110
Justice is what
we all want, dear.

847
00:32:25,194 --> 00:32:25,945
For your father,

848
00:32:26,154 --> 00:32:27,530
and for my client.

849
00:32:31,743 --> 00:32:32,577
You're a mother.

850
00:32:32,994 --> 00:32:33,786
Aren't you?

851
00:32:34,454 --> 00:32:35,121
Yes.

852
00:32:35,663 --> 00:32:36,956
Then shame on you.

853
00:32:43,004 --> 00:32:44,255
We need to talk.

854
00:32:50,428 --> 00:32:51,429
Man, he better be here.

855
00:32:51,679 --> 00:32:53,014
If we can convince him
to give up Perry,

856
00:32:53,848 --> 00:32:55,725
I won't feel so bad about
having slept with Charl...

857
00:32:55,934 --> 00:32:57,268
La la la la!
No more talk

858
00:32:57,477 --> 00:32:59,479
of that disgusting
offense, please.

859
00:33:00,480 --> 00:33:02,398
I thought you said
you hadn't slept with her.

860
00:33:02,857 --> 00:33:05,193
I haven't,
wouldn't ever.

861
00:33:05,401 --> 00:33:06,945
I'm just upset
for the detective.

862
00:33:07,153 --> 00:33:07,862
What, you think I'm not?

863
00:33:08,071 --> 00:33:09,155
I would do anything
to right this.

864
00:33:09,364 --> 00:33:11,199
(sighs):
I know you would.

865
00:33:18,623 --> 00:33:20,875
LAPD! Put your hands
where I can see 'em!

866
00:33:25,463 --> 00:33:26,172
Whoa!

867
00:33:28,007 --> 00:33:30,426
Well, looks like
we found Boris,

868
00:33:30,635 --> 00:33:32,178
at the head
of the table, ironically.

869
00:33:32,387 --> 00:33:35,014
And that's Da Young.
I'd say we were right.

870
00:33:35,223 --> 00:33:36,808
Perry hired him to go
behind the Triad's back

871
00:33:37,016 --> 00:33:39,185
to kill Boris, knowing that
they'd punish him for it.

872
00:33:39,394 --> 00:33:41,854
Clever Perry, killed two birds
with one stone.

873
00:33:42,730 --> 00:33:44,273
Three, if you count
the chicken.

874
00:33:51,155 --> 00:33:52,115
CHLOE:
<i>You've got a lot of nerve.</i>

875
00:33:52,490 --> 00:33:53,491
Yes, I've been told.

876
00:33:53,825 --> 00:33:54,867
And legs for days.

877
00:33:55,076 --> 00:33:57,328
Now, listen,
you're losing bad.

878
00:33:57,537 --> 00:33:59,163
Without Boris, the
prosecution's evidence

879
00:33:59,372 --> 00:34:00,456
is mostly circumstantial.

880
00:34:00,665 --> 00:34:01,958
And, unfortunately for you,

881
00:34:02,166 --> 00:34:03,501
Lucifer's testimony
basically handed me

882
00:34:03,710 --> 00:34:05,044
a non-guilty verdict.

883
00:34:05,253 --> 00:34:07,088
This trial is over.

884
00:34:07,922 --> 00:34:08,798
Maybe.

885
00:34:09,257 --> 00:34:11,342
But the investigation
into that monster

886
00:34:11,551 --> 00:34:13,928
that you call a client
is ongoing.

887
00:34:14,345 --> 00:34:15,805
So one way or another,

888
00:34:16,097 --> 00:34:18,182
- he wi--
- (cell phone rings)

889
00:34:19,100 --> 00:34:19,934
Hmm.

890
00:34:20,143 --> 00:34:20,935
Bad news?

891
00:34:22,145 --> 00:34:23,646
I may have a solution.

892
00:34:25,606 --> 00:34:28,192
My client isn't fully
aware we're winning.

893
00:34:28,401 --> 00:34:29,694
However, he is
more than aware

894
00:34:29,902 --> 00:34:31,029
that he's facing
the death penalty.

895
00:34:31,237 --> 00:34:33,281
And we both know
he's a coward.

896
00:34:34,323 --> 00:34:35,950
I could use
the possibility

897
00:34:36,159 --> 00:34:38,703
of a lethal injection
to get him to plead guilty.

898
00:34:38,911 --> 00:34:39,871
You're supposed to be
on his side.

899
00:34:40,079 --> 00:34:40,913
Why are you doing this?

900
00:34:41,122 --> 00:34:42,498
Well, there is one condition.

901
00:34:43,666 --> 00:34:45,043
You'd have to betray Lucifer.

902
00:34:47,128 --> 00:34:47,795
So...

903
00:34:49,380 --> 00:34:51,215
you want Perry to go to jail,

904
00:34:51,716 --> 00:34:53,134
call Lucifer a liar.

905
00:34:54,218 --> 00:34:55,219
"A liar"?

906
00:34:55,428 --> 00:34:59,057
If there's one thing he cares
about more than anything,

907
00:34:59,932 --> 00:35:01,184
it's his honor.

908
00:35:03,561 --> 00:35:04,520
See you in court.

909
00:35:06,064 --> 00:35:07,106
(clears her throat)

910
00:35:07,732 --> 00:35:08,691
MOM:
<i>Detective Decker,</i>

911
00:35:08,900 --> 00:35:11,110
Lucifer Morningstar
is your partner, correct?

912
00:35:11,319 --> 00:35:11,944
Yes.

913
00:35:12,153 --> 00:35:14,781
He's a civilian
consultant for the LAPD.

914
00:35:14,989 --> 00:35:16,199
We work cases together.

915
00:35:16,407 --> 00:35:18,242
And how is he qualified
for this role?

916
00:35:19,327 --> 00:35:21,996
He is very, uh, intuitive.

917
00:35:22,455 --> 00:35:25,374
He, um, understands
people's desires.

918
00:35:25,583 --> 00:35:26,417
MOM: And in
addition to that,

919
00:35:26,626 --> 00:35:28,419
I assume he studied
law enforcement?

920
00:35:31,339 --> 00:35:32,715
Not to my knowledge, no.

921
00:35:33,466 --> 00:35:34,717
MOM:
Oh, okay.

922
00:35:35,093 --> 00:35:36,427
But he has
a professional background,

923
00:35:36,636 --> 00:35:38,429
which is somehow relevant
to law enforcement?

924
00:35:38,805 --> 00:35:39,722
He owns a nightclub.

925
00:35:39,931 --> 00:35:41,474
MOM:
Okay, but then,

926
00:35:41,682 --> 00:35:44,268
I'm sure his previous job
was more relevant to his role

927
00:35:44,477 --> 00:35:46,187
as a civilian consultant
for the LAPD?

928
00:35:46,395 --> 00:35:48,314
- Right?
- Mm.

929
00:35:49,315 --> 00:35:50,983
Well, if you
believe his claims

930
00:35:51,192 --> 00:35:52,068
that he used to run Hell...

931
00:35:52,485 --> 00:35:54,487
(chokes, clears throat)

932
00:35:55,446 --> 00:35:59,242
...then yes, he's accustomed
to punishing bad guys.

933
00:35:59,450 --> 00:36:00,576
(muffled murmurs)

934
00:36:01,202 --> 00:36:01,869
It's true.

935
00:36:02,078 --> 00:36:03,579
I'm confused, Detective.

936
00:36:03,788 --> 00:36:07,166
Are you suggesting your
partner is delusional,

937
00:36:08,042 --> 00:36:09,252
or just lying?

938
00:36:14,382 --> 00:36:17,301
Lucifer Morningstar
is many things,

939
00:36:18,511 --> 00:36:20,263
but he is not a liar.

940
00:36:20,721 --> 00:36:23,975
Everything that
Mr. Morningstar said

941
00:36:24,392 --> 00:36:26,561
on this stand is
absolutely true.

942
00:36:26,769 --> 00:36:29,564
I was the first person
on that crime scene.

943
00:36:30,064 --> 00:36:32,358
And, yes, I shouldn't
have been anywhere near it.

944
00:36:32,775 --> 00:36:35,111
But I...

945
00:36:36,946 --> 00:36:38,197
let my emotions

946
00:36:38,406 --> 00:36:39,949
get the best of me.

947
00:36:42,451 --> 00:36:43,661
(clears her throat)

948
00:36:45,037 --> 00:36:46,539
Lucifer is the...

949
00:36:48,583 --> 00:36:50,209
...best partner

950
00:36:51,419 --> 00:36:52,837
I have ever had.

951
00:36:53,588 --> 00:36:57,258
And I can only hope that
he can count on me

952
00:36:57,884 --> 00:37:00,344
as much as I count on him.

953
00:37:01,512 --> 00:37:03,514
STEDMAN: Your Honor, we request
the jury be instructed

954
00:37:03,723 --> 00:37:06,684
to disregard Detective Decker's
entire testimony.

955
00:37:06,893 --> 00:37:09,061
We'll take a ten-minute recess.

956
00:37:25,077 --> 00:37:26,204
(overlapping reporter chatter)

957
00:37:26,412 --> 00:37:27,413
REPORTER: Harry,
are you surprised

958
00:37:27,622 --> 00:37:28,706
by that "not guilty" verdict?

959
00:37:28,915 --> 00:37:30,833
No. I'm never surprised
to see justice served.

960
00:37:31,042 --> 00:37:32,335
I believe in our
legal system.

961
00:37:32,543 --> 00:37:33,753
And now I can finally
return to my family

962
00:37:33,961 --> 00:37:35,546
a free man, so,
if you'll excuse me.

963
00:37:35,755 --> 00:37:36,964
(cameras clicking)

964
00:37:37,173 --> 00:37:40,426
(reporters calling for Chloe)

965
00:37:42,678 --> 00:37:45,306
(seagulls squawking)

966
00:38:03,532 --> 00:38:06,202
I'm sorry to bother you,
um, I was, um...

967
00:38:06,869 --> 00:38:08,329
I'm looking for Maze.

968
00:38:08,537 --> 00:38:09,580
Do you know what apartment
she lives in?

969
00:38:09,789 --> 00:38:13,000
Oh, yes, but
she's not home.

970
00:38:15,461 --> 00:38:16,420
Why, did you get
in a fight?

971
00:38:16,629 --> 00:38:18,256
(laughs)

972
00:38:18,464 --> 00:38:19,715
I'm sorry, it's
none of my business.

973
00:38:19,924 --> 00:38:22,134
It's just, my husband...

974
00:38:24,887 --> 00:38:27,265
always gave me flowers
after an argument.

975
00:38:28,349 --> 00:38:30,726
- Are you all right?
- (sighs)

976
00:38:39,318 --> 00:38:40,778
I used to believe

977
00:38:40,987 --> 00:38:42,863
everything happens
for a reason.

978
00:38:43,072 --> 00:38:45,992
But now,
I'm not so sure.

979
00:38:46,742 --> 00:38:47,660
(chuckles)

980
00:38:48,411 --> 00:38:49,161
Me, neither.

981
00:38:51,205 --> 00:38:53,457
But I do know that
no matter how bad things get,

982
00:38:54,292 --> 00:38:56,294
the true test is
how we choose to respond

983
00:38:56,502 --> 00:38:57,837
to the pain we suffer.

984
00:39:00,131 --> 00:39:01,299
Or inflict.

985
00:39:01,507 --> 00:39:02,842
That's well said.

986
00:39:04,093 --> 00:39:05,803
Maze is a lucky girl.

987
00:39:07,722 --> 00:39:09,307
Hope she forgives you.

988
00:39:09,515 --> 00:39:11,267
Ha! Huh.

989
00:39:15,604 --> 00:39:18,524
I'm sorry, you...
you look really familiar.

990
00:39:19,900 --> 00:39:21,152
I'm Chloe's mom?

991
00:39:21,777 --> 00:39:22,820
Have we met?

992
00:39:26,574 --> 00:39:28,242
No, I don't believe we have.

993
00:39:30,077 --> 00:39:31,787
I never forget a face.

994
00:39:34,999 --> 00:39:37,335
If you'll excuse me,
I have to go.

995
00:39:37,668 --> 00:39:38,377
Oh.

996
00:39:41,005 --> 00:39:43,716
♪♪

997
00:39:45,426 --> 00:39:47,887
♪ Nowhere to run
nowhere to hide... ♪

998
00:39:48,304 --> 00:39:49,263
♪ I'm the one... ♪

999
00:39:49,472 --> 00:39:50,890
Good night, Rosie.

1000
00:39:51,098 --> 00:39:53,851
♪ Into the dark
and outta the light ♪

1001
00:39:54,060 --> 00:39:56,687
♪ I'm the one who
goes bump in the night ♪

1002
00:39:56,896 --> 00:39:58,481
♪♪

1003
00:39:59,065 --> 00:39:59,899
Perry Smith.

1004
00:40:03,361 --> 00:40:04,862
I know you had
Boris killed.

1005
00:40:06,530 --> 00:40:07,740
I also know
you're responsible

1006
00:40:07,948 --> 00:40:09,575
for the murder
of Joe Fields

1007
00:40:10,493 --> 00:40:11,285
and John Decker.

1008
00:40:11,494 --> 00:40:14,497
Aw, such a shame there's
no evidence, right?

1009
00:40:14,997 --> 00:40:17,375
The system kind of needs proof.

1010
00:40:18,584 --> 00:40:19,543
Yeah.

1011
00:40:19,752 --> 00:40:22,046
You clean your mess,
we got nada.

1012
00:40:22,463 --> 00:40:24,340
But you know who's
okay with nada?

1013
00:40:24,548 --> 00:40:26,092
Or shall I say <i>nichego?</i>

1014
00:40:27,968 --> 00:40:28,969
Yeah, that's right.

1015
00:40:29,178 --> 00:40:30,471
You see, the Russians,

1016
00:40:31,222 --> 00:40:32,264
they don't like it
when one of their own

1017
00:40:32,473 --> 00:40:34,058
is taken out
without permission.

1018
00:40:35,393 --> 00:40:36,435
But who knows?

1019
00:40:37,603 --> 00:40:38,771
Maybe they won't hear about it.

1020
00:40:45,694 --> 00:40:46,404
Whoa.

1021
00:40:46,612 --> 00:40:48,239
Aah!
(muffled shouting)

1022
00:40:50,991 --> 00:40:52,201
My pleasure, Misha.

1023
00:40:52,410 --> 00:40:53,619
<i>Do svidanya.</i>

1024
00:41:00,876 --> 00:41:03,921
(tires screeching)

1025
00:41:04,463 --> 00:41:06,298
♪ I'm the one that goes
bump in the night... ♪

1026
00:41:06,507 --> 00:41:07,716
I didn't think
you had it in you.

1027
00:41:08,300 --> 00:41:09,468
I'm impressed.

1028
00:41:10,678 --> 00:41:11,345
Drive.

1029
00:41:11,554 --> 00:41:12,847
♪ That goes bump in the night ♪

1030
00:41:13,055 --> 00:41:15,433
♪ I'm the one, I'm the one ♪

1031
00:41:15,641 --> 00:41:16,892
♪ I'm the one ♪

1032
00:41:17,101 --> 00:41:19,645
♪ I'm the one and only one. ♪

1033
00:41:35,703 --> 00:41:36,871
You were right.

1034
00:41:38,789 --> 00:41:40,583
You are nothing like Father.

1035
00:41:41,542 --> 00:41:44,128
Oh? What changed
your mind?

1036
00:41:44,628 --> 00:41:47,590
If I tell you this, you have to come
completely clean with me, Mother.

1037
00:41:48,257 --> 00:41:50,926
No more secrets, Mom.
No more lies.

1038
00:41:53,846 --> 00:41:54,638
Okay.

1039
00:41:56,765 --> 00:41:58,225
What happened?

1040
00:41:59,101 --> 00:42:00,936
35 years ago, Father,

1041
00:42:02,146 --> 00:42:03,314
He asked me
to come down here

1042
00:42:03,522 --> 00:42:05,483
to bless a couple who was
unable to have a child.

1043
00:42:05,858 --> 00:42:07,818
He had never asked me
to do anything of this sort,

1044
00:42:08,027 --> 00:42:09,487
and He never did again.

1045
00:42:11,071 --> 00:42:11,780
Today...

1046
00:42:13,532 --> 00:42:15,242
I met the mother again.

1047
00:42:17,703 --> 00:42:19,371
And I found out what the result

1048
00:42:19,580 --> 00:42:21,081
of that miracle was.

1049
00:42:23,167 --> 00:42:24,293
Or, rather, who.

1050
00:42:24,502 --> 00:42:25,503
(elevator bell dings)

1051
00:42:28,506 --> 00:42:29,965
- CHLOE: Oh, hey.
- LUCIFER: Detective.

1052
00:42:30,174 --> 00:42:32,301
- CHLOE: Sorry, I thought...
- LUCIFER: What are you doing here?

1053
00:42:33,010 --> 00:42:34,011
Are you on your way out?

1054
00:42:34,678 --> 00:42:35,846
I am, yes.

1055
00:42:36,388 --> 00:42:37,473
- Oh...
- To see you, actually.

1056
00:42:38,974 --> 00:42:39,600
Oh.

1057
00:42:40,518 --> 00:42:42,019
I believe I owe you dinner.

1058
00:42:44,104 --> 00:42:46,690
MOM:
<i>Now we know why
Chloe's so special.</i>

1059
00:42:46,899 --> 00:42:47,775
Don't we?

1060
00:42:49,485 --> 00:42:50,986
Your Father put her here.

1061
00:42:51,904 --> 00:42:53,614
In Lucifer's path.

1062
00:42:56,158 --> 00:42:57,284
You know what this means?

1063
00:42:57,493 --> 00:43:00,913
It means...
that I was a pawn.

1064
00:43:01,121 --> 00:43:04,833
♪ Can you feel it
coming in the air tonight ♪

1065
00:43:05,042 --> 00:43:05,918
Say when.

1066
00:43:06,126 --> 00:43:07,211
- When!
- (laughter)

1067
00:43:07,419 --> 00:43:08,796
When.

1068
00:43:09,004 --> 00:43:10,214
I hope you know
it takes months

1069
00:43:10,422 --> 00:43:11,840
to get a reservation
at this place.

1070
00:43:12,049 --> 00:43:13,551
Oh, yeah.
The fries are amazing.

1071
00:43:13,759 --> 00:43:15,344
Oh, thank you.
I made them myself.

1072
00:43:18,264 --> 00:43:20,516
It means Chloe's
not an obstacle.

1073
00:43:21,684 --> 00:43:23,769
She's how you'll
get your wings back.

1074
00:43:23,978 --> 00:43:26,564
She's how we'll
get it all back.

1075
00:43:27,731 --> 00:43:30,568
♪ But I don't know
if you know... ♪

1076
00:43:30,776 --> 00:43:31,652
Detective?

1077
00:43:32,403 --> 00:43:34,280
What you said
today in the courtroom...

1078
00:43:35,531 --> 00:43:36,991
It was the truth.

1079
00:43:37,199 --> 00:43:39,952
♪ In the air tonight ♪

1080
00:43:40,578 --> 00:43:42,288
♪ Oh, Lord ♪

1081
00:43:44,623 --> 00:43:46,959
♪ I've been waiting
for this moment ♪

1082
00:43:47,251 --> 00:43:48,961
We're going home, son.

1083
00:43:50,004 --> 00:43:53,591
And Chloe is the Key.

1084
00:43:54,675 --> 00:43:56,885
♪ I can feel it coming ♪

1085
00:43:57,094 --> 00:44:00,097
♪ In the air tonight ♪

1086
00:44:00,681 --> 00:44:02,349
♪ Oh, Lord. ♪

